## 1. Final Proposed FYP Title

**Feasibility Study and Prototype Development of a Semi-Automated Preventive Maintenance System for OHT Mark 2 Obstacle Detection Sensors**

---

## 2. Core Project Idea

The project aims to improve the current preventive maintenance workflow for **Overhead Hoist Transport (OHT) Mark 2 obstacle detection sensors** used in the **Automated Material Handling System (AMHS)** environment.

The current PM process is manual and requires technicians to:

- connect to multiple sensor ports
- simulate obstacle / non-obstacle conditions
- interpret sensor readings
- make minor adjustments where required
- capture screenshots or records as PM evidence
- manually follow the PM sequence

The proposed project is to create a **semi-automated technician-in-the-loop PM workflow**, supported by:

- offline PM guidance software
- local file logging and screenshot capture
- possible live sensor display integration
- possible camera / vision feedback
- evaluation of docking / connector handling concepts
- feasibility study of suitable hardware implementation methods

The project is **not meant to guarantee full production deployment**. It is framed as a **prototype-level feasibility study**.

---

## 3. Scope Positioning

The project should be positioned as:

> **workflow study + offline software prototype + feasibility evaluation of sensor docking / connector handling methods**

The project should **not** be positioned as:

> full deployment of a production-ready robot system

This is important because the project is a WSDeg FYP with limited time commitment, approximately up to 2 days per week across 1 year.

